{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778466995856,"sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-a0b84afff0cb6a63","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"Following the edits in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770 last year (June 2025), the current tree under 'protein O-linked glycosylation' looks like this:\\n<img width=\\\"452\\\" height=\\\"131\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8cfbdafa-a21b-4555-97b3-7501c99211dc\\\" />\\n\\nHowever, is seems that one of the new terms requested in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770 was not made:\\n**protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine** (referred to as 'protein O-linked GlcNAcylation' in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770)\\n\\nThis term is needed to annotate fly Ogt and Eogt (see https://flybase.org/reports/FBgg0002104) and orthologs.\\nThe term was also requested back in 2022 in #23575, but it was not made then because \\\"This corresponds to the MF protein GO:0097363 O-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity, since it is a single reaction.\\\"\\n\\nIt's true that adding GlcNAc is a single-step event and the sugar isn't further extended - the process is actually reversible and seems more similar to phosphorylation than the other O-linked glycosylations (see PMID: 35536957). Nonetheless, I think we need a distinct BP term for this so that the relevant genes can be annotated to same level of granularity as (and thus be distinguished from) the current sister terms. (Currently, Ogt/Eogt are annotated to the generic parent term 'protein O-linked glycosylation')\\n\\n\\n* **Suggested term label:**\\nprotein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\\n\\n* **Definition (free text)**\\nA glycoprotein biosynthetic process in which a single N-acetylglucosamine is covalently linked via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or threonine side chain in a protein, resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. The sugar is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\\n\\n* **Reference, in format PMID:#######**\\nPMID: 35536957\\n\\n\\n* **Gene product name and ID to ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"NTR: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32044\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"Following the edits in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770 last year (June 2025), the current tree under 'protein O-linked glycosylation' looks like this:\\n<img width=\\\"452\\\" height=\\\"131\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8cfbdafa-a21b-4555-97b3-7501c99211dc\\\" />\\n\\nHowever, is seems that one of the new terms requested in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770 was not made:\\n**protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine** (referred to as 'protein O-linked GlcNAcylation' in https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29770)\\n\\nThis term is needed to annotate fly Ogt and Eogt (see https://flybase.org/reports/FBgg0002104) and orthologs.\\nThe term was also requested back in 2022 in #23575, but it was not made then because \\\"This corresponds to the MF protein GO:0097363 O-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity, since it is a single reaction.\\\"\\n\\nIt's true that adding GlcNAc is a single-step event and the sugar isn't further extended - the process is actually reversible and seems more similar to phosphorylation than the other O-linked glycosylations (see PMID: 35536957). Nonetheless, I think we need a distinct BP term for this so that the relevant genes can be annotated to same level of granularity as (and thus be distinguished from) the current sister terms. (Currently, Ogt/Eogt are annotated to the generic parent term 'protein O-linked glycosylation')\\n\\n\\n* **Suggested term label:**\\nprotein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\\n\\n* **Definition (free text)**\\nA glycoprotein biosynthetic process in which a single N-acetylglucosamine is covalently linked via a beta-glycosidic bond to the oxygen atom of a serine or threonine side chain in a protein, resulting in the formation of a protein O-linked glycan. The sugar is not elongated into a larger oligosaccharide chain.\\n\\n* **Reference, in format PMID:#######**\\nPMID: 35536957\\n\\n\\n* **Gene product name and ID to ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"NTR: protein O-linked glycosylation via N-acetylglucosamine\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32044\"\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778466995845,"end":1778466995854}},"id":"prt_e14e4bb500019yXJ8zTOwL5Zhp","sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","messageID":"msg_e14e4b87c001f27gjCkRVVS1rU"}}
