{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778467078116,"sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-8ce3d3d9a3ffe5db","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/src/ontology/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: all: stage_release\n2: \n3: SHELL=./stamp.sh\n4: \n5: # ----------------------------------------\n6: # CORE VARIABLES\n7: # ----------------------------------------\n8: \n9: # base URI for all OBO library ontologies\n10: OBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n11: \n12: # OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\n13: ONT=go\n14: \n15: # Base URL for ontology\n16: BASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n17: \n18: # Source file edited by editors\n19: SRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n20: \n21: # Staging release directory\n22: RELEASEDIR=../../target\n23: RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS=$(RELEASEDIR)/imports\n24: \n25: # ROBOT is the main release release tool\n26: ROBOT_ENV = ROBOT_JAVA_ARGS=-Xmx12G\n27: ROBOT = $(ROBOT_ENV) robot --catalog catalog-v001.xml\n28: \n29: # OWLTools is a swiss-army knife;\n30: # It does some things robot can't do, but eventually functionality should\n31: # move to robot\n32: OWLTOOLS_ENV = OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=6G\n33: OWLTOOLS = $(OWLTOOLS_ENV) owltools\n34: \n35: #DOSDP is used for turning tsv files into pieces of ontologies for imports\n36: DOSDP_ENV = JAVA_OPTS=-Xmx6G\n37: DOSDP_TOOLS = $(DOSDP_ENV) dosdp-tools\n38: \n39: SCALA_CLI = scala-cli run --server=false --java-opt=-Xmx6g\n40: \n41: # OWL catalogs map ontology IRIs to local paths\n42: USECAT= --use-catalog\n43: \n44: # obo-centric checks and and filters\n45: PERLCHECK= ../util/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n46: PERLFILTER= ../util/filter-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n47: \n48: # Release IRIs are of the form\n49: #  obo/go/releases/YYYY-MM-DD/$FILE\n50: #\n51: # To make snapshot releases:\n52: #\n53: #   $ RELEASE_SUFFIX=SNAPSHOT make prepare_release\n54: #\n55: RELEASEDATE ?= `date +%Y-%m-%d`\n56: RELEASE_SUFFIX=\n57: RELEASE_URIBASE = $(BASE)/releases/$(RELEASEDATE)$(RELEASE_SUFFIX)\n58: \n59: # basic relations are part_of & 3 regulations relations\n60: GO_BASIC_RELATIONS = BFO:0000050 RO:0002211 RO:0002212 RO:0002213\n61: \n62: # extend with has_part, occurs_in and during relations\n63: # - this is the set used in the main go file\n64: GO_MAIN_RELATIONS = $(GO_BASIC_RELATIONS) BFO:0000051 BFO:0000066 RO:0002091 RO:0002092 RO:0002093\n65: \n66: GO_PLUS = extensions/go-plus\n67: GO_GAF = extensions/go-gaf\n68: GO_AMIGO = extensions/go-amigo\n69: GO_LEGO = extensions/go-lego\n70: GO_LEGO_REACTO = extensions/go-lego-reacto\n71: \n72: SPARQLDIR = ../sparql\n73: REPORTDIR = $(RELEASEDIR)/reports\n74: \n75: # ----------------------------------------\n76: # TOP LEVEL TARGETS\n77: # ----------------------------------------\n78: \n79: stage_release: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl test $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json.gz $(GO_PLUS).owl $(GO_PLUS).json.gz go-base.owl $(GO_GAF).owl $(GO_AMIGO).owl $(GO_LEGO).owl $(GO_LEGO_REACTO).owl go-basic.obo go-basic.json.gz extensions/rhea-reactions.ttl imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.obo subset-owls subset-reports generate-mappings\n80: \n81: test: datalog-violations.tsv $(SRC)-check basic-cycles.tsv sparql_test check_all_taxon_constraints_columns change-report.txt reasoned.ofn unsatisfiable present_in_taxon_check.ofn chebi_pH_7_3_check\n82: \n83: travis_test: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns datalog-violations.tsv chebi_pH_7_3_check $(SRC)-check travis_build change-report.txt\n84: \n85: # This target combines features from reasoned.ofn, enhanced.ofn, sparql_test into a faster mode for Travis/GitHub Actions.\n86: # These must be kept in sync.\n87: # The convert step is here only to work around https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1250\n88: travis_build: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn\n89: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(VARGS) -O reports/ merge --collapse-import-closure false -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl remove --term 'IAO:0000116' --axioms annotation --signature true query --update ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru remove --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'oboInOwl:source' reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce annotate -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -o travis_build_dummy_out.ofn verify --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/multiple-class-links-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/missing_superclass-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/different-namespace-violation.sparql -O reports/\n90: \n91: unsatisfiable: $(GO_GAF).owl\n92: \t$(ROBOT) reason --reasoner ELK --input extensions/go-gaf.owl -D $(RELEASEDIR)/core_dump.owl || true\n93: \n94: full_test: test $(ONT).obo\n95: \n96: # note that most derived files are kept separate from source files, in $(RELEASEDIR)\n97: clean: clean_target clean_imports\n98: clean_target:\n99: \trm -rf $(RELEASEDIR)/*\n100: \n101: # copies from staged area to target\n102: prepare_release:\n103: \techo \"Base Version IRI: $(RELEASE_URIBASE)\"\n104: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n105: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets &&\\\n106: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n107: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n108: \tmkdir -p $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n109: \tcp $(ONT).owl $(ONT).obo $(ONT).json $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n110: \tcp imports/*.owl $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n111: \tcp imports/*.obo $(RELEASEDIR_IMPORTS) &&\\\n112: \tcp extensions/* $(RELEASEDIR)/extensions &&\\\n113: \tcp external2go/* $(RELEASEDIR)/external2go &&\\\n114: \tcp go-basic.* $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n115: \tcp go-base.owl $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n116: \tfind subsets/ -maxdepth 1 -type f ! -name '*.tmp' -exec cp {} $(RELEASEDIR)/subsets/ \\; &&\\\n117: \tcp reports/* $(RELEASEDIR)/reports &&\\\n118: \techo \"Release files are now in $(RELEASEDIR)\"\n119: \n120: # deploy to S3\n121: # URLs will be of the form https://s3.amazonaws.com/go-data-product-current/ontology/subsets/go-basic.json.gz\n122: S3CFG = ~/.s3cfg.go-pipeline-push-agent\n123: # https://build.berkeleybop.org/job/release-go-ontology-daily-snapshot/\n124: deploy-snapshot:\n125: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n126: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-snapshot/ontology/\n127: \n128: deploy-release:\n129: \tcd $(RELEASEDIR) &&\\\n130: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-current/ontology/\n131: \ts3cmd -c $(S3CFG) --acl-public --mime-type=application/rdf+xml sync ./  s3://go-data-product-release/$(RELEASEDATE)/ontology/\n132: \n133: \n134: # ----------------------------------------\n135: # GENERIC TRANSFORMS\n136: # ----------------------------------------\n137: \n138: %.gz: %\n139: \tgzip -c $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n140: \n141: %.json: %.ofn\n142: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input $< -f json -o $@\n143: .PRECIOUS: %.json\n144: \n145: # ----------------------------------------\n146: # CHECKS AND BALANCES\n147: # ----------------------------------------\n148: \n149: # TODO: use json form of this file\n150: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/13837\n151: # See also: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18870\n152: GO.xrf_abbs: $(SRC)\n153: \twget http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/db-xrefs.legacy -O $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@ && touch $@\n154: \n155: $(SRC)-check: $(SRC) GO.xrf_abbs\n156: \t$(PERLCHECK) --disable-isa-incomplete --disable-whitespace-check --xref-abbs GO.xrf_abbs $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n157: \n158: # consider using snapshot release\n159: PREVIOUS=go-lastrelease.owl\n160: PREVIOUS_OBO=go-lastrelease.obo\n161: PREVIOUS_PLUS=go-plus-lastrelease.owl\n162: $(PREVIOUS): $(SRC)\n163: \twget $(OBO)/go.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n164: \n165: $(PREVIOUS_OBO): $(SRC)\n166: \twget $(OBO)/go.obo -O $@ && touch $@\n167: \n168: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS): $(SRC)\n169: \twget $(OBO)/go/extensions/go-plus.owl -O $@ && touch $@\n170: \n171: # ensure no IDs are lost\n172: change-report.txt: $(SRC) $(PREVIOUS)\n173: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $(USECAT) $< --verify-changes -p $(PREVIOUS) -o $@ --id-prefix-filter GO: --check-missing-labels && touch $@\n174: \n175: go-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS) go.ofn\n176: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS) --right go.ofn --format markdown -o $@\n177: \n178: go-plus-owl-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n179: \t$(ROBOT) diff --left $(PREVIOUS_PLUS) --right $(GO_PLUS).ofn --format markdown -o $@\n180: \n181: go-obo-txt-diff.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo\n182: \t{ echo \"# Textual diff for go.obo\\\\n\"; echo \"\\`\\`\\`diff\"; diff -u $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo; echo \"\\`\\`\\`\"; } >$@\n183: \n184: go-obo-status.md: $(PREVIOUS_OBO) go.obo ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md\n185: \t{ echo \"---\"; runoak -i simpleobo:go.obo statistics --group-by-obo-namespace --compare-with simpleobo:$(PREVIOUS_OBO); echo \"---\"; cat ../gh_pages_templates/go-obo-status.md; } >$@\n186: \n187: # ----------------------------------------\n188: # OWL\n189: # ----------------------------------------\n190: \n191: #Uses file provided by Reactome to generate xrefs for import\n192: \n193: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt:\n194: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n195: \n196: ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt:\n197: \twget -O $@ --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n198: \n199: imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl: ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n200: \tmkdir -p reactome-tmp\n201: \tsed -i '1s/.*/Identifier\\tName\\tdefined_class/' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n202: \tsed -i '1d' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n203: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt\n204: \tperl -i.bak -pe 's/[^[:ascii:]]//g' ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt\n205: \tcat ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt >reactome-tmp/combined.txt\n206: \trm ../resources/Reactions2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n207: \trm ../resources/Pathways2GoTerms_human.txt.bak\n208: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --template=xref_dosdp_yaml/reactome_xref.yaml --infile=reactome-tmp/combined.txt --outfile=reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --obo-prefixes=true\n209: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input reactome-tmp/reactome_xrefs.ofn --output imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl annotate --ontology-iri $(BASE)/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n210: \n211: # Remove reactome_xrefs_import.owl and go_taxon_constraints.owl from imports. These are merged in directly in enhanced.ofn\n212: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo: $(SRC)\n213: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl' $< |\\\n214: \tgrep -v '^import: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl' >$@\n215: \n216: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn: go-edit-trimmed-imports.obo ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc ../resources/rhea.rdf\n217: \t$(SCALA_CLI) ../util/filter-rhea-xrefs.sc -- $< catalog-v001.xml ../resources/rhea.rdf $@\n218: \n219: # merge in some imported GO modules\n220: # remove editor-only annotations\n221: # convert some xrefs to skos properties - only for prefixes defined in the SPARQL update file\n222: # NOTE - the beginning 'annotate' command is used only to work around this ROBOT bug when merge is the first command: \n223: # https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1250\n224: # NOTE - 'convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld' is necessary until ROBOT issue https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1266 is fixed\n225: enhanced.ofn: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru\n226: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/reactome_xrefs_import.owl -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl remove --term 'IAO:0000116' --axioms annotation --signature true query --update ../sparql/add-skos-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-broad-xrefs.ru --update ../sparql/remove-related-xrefs.ru remove --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'oboInOwl:source' annotate --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -o $@\n227: \n228: # reasoned.ofn is equivalent to editors source, after materialize-reason-relax-reduce pipeline\n229: # note: we keep this as a distinct intermediate target as the ontology IRI needs to be 'go' for Oort to work...\n230: reasoned.ofn: enhanced.ofn $(SRC)-check\n231: \t$(ROBOT) materialize -i $< -r ELK --term BFO:0000050 reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce annotate -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl -o $@\n232: \n233: present_in_taxon_check.ofn: enhanced.ofn ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn\n234: \t$(ROBOT) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i $< -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn reason -r ELK -e asserted-only --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural -o $@\n235: \n236: # equivalent to reasoned, but we rename\n237: # TODO cleanup redundancies with merge here and with go-base\n238: # note: do not run 'reason' after go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl is merged; some desired logical redundancy may be lost\n239: $(GO_PLUS).ofn: reasoned.ofn imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl\n240: \t$(ROBOT) unmerge -i $< -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl merge --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false merge -i imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n241: \n242: $(GO_PLUS).owl: $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n243: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n244: .PRECIOUS: $(GO_PLUS).owl\n245: \n246: # Create release file containing GO-asserted axioms, no external axioms.\n247: # GO artifacts to merge are hardcoded here.\n248: go-base.owl: $(GO_PLUS).ofn\n249: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select imports --trim false remove --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GOREL_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GOCHE_' --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_Union_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false merge -i extensions/go-gci.owl -i extensions/go-bridge.owl -i extensions/ro_pending.owl -i imports/x-disjoint.ofn annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n250: \n251: $(GO_GAF).owl: extensions/go-gaf-edit.ofn $(GO_PLUS).owl extensions/gorel.owl mirror/cl.owl mirror/taxslim.owl mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl\n252: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n253: \n254: $(GO_AMIGO).owl: extensions/go-amigo-edit.ofn $(GO_GAF).owl extensions/go-modules-annotations.owl extensions/go-taxon-subsets.owl mirror/eco.owl mirror/pato.owl mirror/po.owl mirror/chebi.owl mirror/uberon.owl mirror/wbbt.owl\n255: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n256: \n257: # Not all imports are being pre-mirrored; the ones that are should be dependencies\n258: $(GO_LEGO).owl: extensions/go-lego-edit.ofn $(GO_PLUS).owl mirror/ro.owl extensions/legorel.owl extensions/go-bfo-bridge.owl mirror/taxslim.owl mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl mirror/cl.owl mirror/uberon.owl mirror/users.ttl mirror/groups.ttl imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl mirror/wbbt.owl mirror/eco.owl\n259: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce --named-classes-only true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n260: \n261: extensions/reacto.owl: $(GO_LEGO).owl mirror/chebi.owl\n262: \tmkdir -p reacto-tmp\n263: \twget -O ./reacto-tmp/biopax2go.jar --no-check-certificate https://github.com/geneontology/pathways2GO/releases/download/v1.1.4/biopax2go.jar\n264: \twget -O ./reacto-tmp/biopax.zip --no-check-certificate https://reactome.org/download/current/biopax.zip\n265: \tunzip -o ./reacto-tmp/biopax.zip -d ./reacto-tmp/\n266: \tjava -jar -Xmx8G ./reacto-tmp/biopax2go.jar -b ./reacto-tmp/Homo_sapiens.owl -reacto ./extensions/reacto -lego $(GO_LEGO).owl -chebi ./mirror/chebi.owl\n267: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i extensions/reacto.ttl -o extensions/reacto.owl\n268: \trm ./reacto-tmp/*\n269: \trmdir ./reacto-tmp\n270: \n271: $(GO_LEGO_REACTO).owl: extensions/go-lego-reacto-edit.ofn $(GO_LEGO).owl extensions/reacto.owl\n272: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< --collapse-import-closure true --include-annotations false reason -r ELK --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --remove-redundant-subclass-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural relax reduce --named-classes-only true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n273: \n274: # ----------------------------------------\n275: # OBO and subsets\n276: # ----------------------------------------\n277: \n278: # while go-plus is the full version, the successive releases eliminate various things to simplify the\n279: # file, including\n280: #  - no imports or external ontologies\n281: #  - smaller set of relations (v small for go-basic)\n282: #  - ...\n283: # go.obo is a simplified; we use oort to remove imports etc\n284: $(ONT)-pre.ofn: reasoned.ofn\n285: \t$(ROBOT) materialize --input $< --reasoner ELK $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_MAIN_RELATIONS)) remove --select imports --trim true remove --select '<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_*>' --select complement --select classes --signature true --trim true remove $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_MAIN_RELATIONS)) --select complement --select object-properties --signature true --trim true annotate -O $(OBO)/$(ONT).owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$(ONT).owl convert -f owl --output $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n286: \n287: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn: $(ONT)-pre.ofn\n288: \t$(ROBOT) reduce -r elk -i $< -o $@\n289: .PRECIOUS: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn\n290: \n291: go.ofn: $(ONT)-pre-reduced.ofn\n292: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select 'complement' --drop-axiom-annotations 'IAO:0000233' -o $@\n293: \n294: go.owl: go.ofn\n295: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n296: \n297: go.obo: $(ONT).ofn\n298: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@.tmp.obo &&\\\n299: \tcp $@.tmp.obo $@\n300: #\t$(PERLCHECK) --disable-xrf-abbs-check --disable-multiply-labeled-edge --disable-whitespace-check $@.tmp.obo\n301: \n302: # remove non-basic relationship types (e.g. has_part)\n303: # assuming materialization step already done for these properties when making go.obo\n304: # NOTE - '--add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld' is necessary due to https://github.com/ontodev/robot/issues/1266\n305: go-simple-filtered.ofn: go.ofn $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-cross-namespace-relations.ru $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-mf-regulates-links.ru $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-multiply-labeled-edges.ru\n306: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< $(addprefix --term ,$(GO_BASIC_RELATIONS)) --select complement --select object-properties --signature true --trim true remove --term 'oboInOwl:created_by' --term 'oboInOwl:creation_date' --term 'IAO:0000233' --term 'IAO:0000589' --term 'RO:0002175' --signature true --trim true remove --axioms \"DisjointClasses EquivalentClasses\" query --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-cross-namespace-relations.ru --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-mf-regulates-links.ru --update $(SPARQLDIR)/remove-multiply-labeled-edges.ru convert --add-prefixes prefixes.jsonld -f ofn --output $@\n307: \n308: go-basic.ofn: go-simple-filtered.ofn\n309: \t$(ROBOT) reduce -r elk -i $< -o $@\n310: \n311: go-basic.owl: go-basic.ofn\n312: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n313: #FIXME rewrite perl filter/check\n314: #\t$(PERLFILTER) $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@ && $(PERLCHECK) --disable-xrf-abbs-check --disable-whitespace-check $@\n315: \n316: go-basic.obo: go-basic.ofn\n317: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n318: \n319: # check for cycles in go-basic\n320: basic.facts: go-basic.owl\n321: \triot -q --output=ntriples $< | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >$@\n322: \n323: basic-cycles.tsv: basic.facts ../util/cycles.dl\n324: \tsouffle ../util/cycles.dl && mv cycle.csv $@ &&\\\n325: \t( [ -s $@ ] && { cat $@; exit 1; } || true ) # exit with an error if the output is not empty\n326: \n327: # ----------------------------------------\n328: # SUBSETS AND REPORTS\n329: # ----------------------------------------\n330: # Currently the only per-subset report is id-label pairs\n331: # See: https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/14028\n332: \n333: PUBLISH_SUBSETS = gocheck_do_not_annotate gocheck_obsoletion_candidate goslim_agr goslim_candida goslim_chembl goslim_drosophila goslim_euk_cellular_processes_ribbon goslim_flybase_ribbon goslim_generic goslim_metagenomics goslim_mouse goslim_pir goslim_plant goslim_plant_ribbon goslim_pombe goslim_prokaryote_ribbon goslim_synapse goslim_yeast goslim_prokaryote goslim_virus\n334: \n335: SUBSET_OWLS = $(patsubst %,subsets/%.owl,$(PUBLISH_SUBSETS))\n336: subset-owls: $(SUBSET_OWLS)\n337: \n338: # Also generates %.obo and %.json\n339: subsets/subset-terms.tsv: $(ONT).owl $(SPARQLDIR)/subset-terms.sparql\n340: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -f tsv --query $(word 2,$^) $@\n341: \n342: subsets/subset-properties.tsv: $(ONT).owl $(SPARQLDIR)/subset-properties.sparql\n343: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -f tsv --query $(word 2,$^) $@.tmp && sed 's/\"//g' $@.tmp >$@ && rm -f $@.tmp\n344: \n345: subsets/%-terms.txt: subsets/subset-terms.tsv subsets/subset-properties.tsv\n346: \tgrep '\"$*\"' $< | cut -f1 | sed 's/\"//g' >$@.tmp && cat $@.tmp $(word 2,$^) >$@ && rm -f $@.tmp\n347: \n348: # Also generates %.obo and %.json\n349: subsets/%.owl: $(ONT).ofn subsets/%-terms.txt\n350: \t$(ROBOT) extract --method subset -i $< --term-file $(word 2,$^) annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ --annotation owl:versionInfo $(RELEASEDATE) -o $@ convert -o $(patsubst %.owl,%.obo,$@) convert -o $(patsubst %.owl,%.json,$@)\n351: \n352: # so far we only make simple .tsv reports\n353: SUBSET_REPORTS = $(patsubst %,%.tsv,$(basename $(SUBSET_OWLS)))\n354: subset-reports: $(SUBSET_REPORTS)\n355: subsets/%.tsv: subsets/%.owl\n356: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< -s ../sparql/labels.sparql $@\n357: \n358: # ----------------------------------------\n359: # IMPORT MODULES\n360: # ----------------------------------------\n361: \n362: IMPORTS = chebi cl po pato ro ncbitaxon uberon ddanat fao oba so opl reactome_xrefs go_taxon_constraints\n363: IMPORTS_OWL = $(patsubst %, imports/%_import.owl,$(IMPORTS)) $(patsubst %, imports/%_import.obo,$(IMPORTS))\n364: \n365: # Make this target to regenerate ALL\n366: all_imports: $(IMPORTS_OWL)\n367: clean_imports:\n368: \trm mirror/*\n369: \n370: seed.txt: enhanced.ofn imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl\n371: \t$(ROBOT) merge --collapse-import-closure false -i enhanced.ofn -i imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl -i imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl -i ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn -i imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl query -f csv --select ../sparql/terms.sparql $@\n372: \n373: # Specialize seed terms for PR. The inclusion of taxon IRIs in the full seed was causing PR to pull\n374: # in overly specific proteins (e.g. human forms of everything) and referencing gene IRIs. This is kind\n375: # of a general problem to balance for all import module extractions; need to come up with a consistent approach.\n376: imports/pr_terms_combined.txt: imports/pr_terms.txt seed.txt\n377: \tcat $^ | grep 'PR_' > $@\n378: \n379: # Specialize seed terms for OPL.\n380: imports/opl_terms_combined.txt: imports/opl_terms.txt seed.txt\n381: \tcat $^ | grep 'OPL_' > $@\n382: \n383: imports/%_terms_combined.txt: imports/%_terms.txt seed.txt\n384: \tcat $^ > $@\n385: \n386: # Use ROBOT for imports\n387: \n388: imports/%_import_pre.owl: mirror/%.owl imports/%_terms_combined.txt $(SRC)\n389: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< -T imports/$*_terms_combined.txt --method BOT reason --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural annotate -O $(BASE)/imports/$*_import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/imports/$*_import.owl -o $@\n390: .PRECIOUS: imports/%_import_pre.owl\n391: \n392: imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl: imports/ncbitaxon_import_pre.owl ../sparql/add-taxon-sibling-disjoints.ru ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru\n393: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< --update ../sparql/add-taxon-sibling-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru -o $@\n394: \n395: # Ensure every row in the taxon constraints files has the same number of columns (only one line should be output by `sort`)\n396: check_taxon_constraint_columns_%: ../taxon_constraints/%.tsv\n397: \tawk -F'\\t' '{print NF}' $< | sort -nu | wc -l | sed -e 's/[[:blank:]]//g' | grep -q \"^1$$\" && exit 0 || (echo \"ERROR: wrong number of columns in $<. Check for spaces where tabs should be.\" && exit 1)\n398: \n399: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns: check_taxon_constraint_columns_only_in_taxon check_taxon_constraint_columns_never_in_taxon check_taxon_constraint_columns_present_in_taxon\n400: \n401: .PHONY: check_all_taxon_constraints_columns\n402: \n403: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.tsv\n404: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n405: \n406: ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.tsv\n407: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n408: \n409: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.yaml ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv\n410: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv --generate-defined-class=true --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n411: \n412: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.ofn: ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.yaml ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv\n413: \techo 'defined_class\tdefined_class_label\ttaxon\ttaxon_label\tsource' >../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv &&\\\n414: \ttail -n +2 ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon.tsv >>../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv &&\\\n415: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --infile=../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.tsv --obo-prefixes=true --template=$< --outfile=$@\n416: \n417: imports/go_taxon_constraints.owl: ../taxon_constraints/only_in_taxon.ofn ../taxon_constraints/never_in_taxon.ofn ../taxon_constraints/present_in_taxon_annotations.ofn\n418: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(addprefix -i , $^) annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n419: \n420: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl: $(SRC) $(SPARQLDIR)/taxon-constraints-materialization.ru ../util/materialize-taxon-constraints.dl\n421: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< query --update $(SPARQLDIR)/taxon-constraints-materialization.ru -o taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.ofn &&\\\n422: \tJAVA_OPTS=-Xmx12G relation-graph --ontology-file taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.ofn --output-file taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.nt --property 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162' --output-subclasses true --reflexive-subclasses false &&\\\n423: \tsed 's/ /\\t/' taxon-constraints-materialization-temp.nt | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >taxonconstraintsrelationgraph.facts &&\\\n424: \tsouffle ../util/materialize-taxon-constraints.dl &&\\\n425: \tsed -E 's|<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/([^[:space:]]+)_([[:digit:]]+)>|\\1:\\2|g' computed_only_in_taxon.csv | sed '1s/^/defined_class\\ttaxon\\n/' >computed_only_in_taxon.tsv &&\\\n426: \tsed -E 's|<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/([^[:space:]]+)_([[:digit:]]+)>|\\1:\\2|g' computed_never_in_taxon.csv | sed '1s/^/defined_class\\ttaxon\\n/' >computed_never_in_taxon.tsv &&\\\n427: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --template=../taxon_constraints/computed_only_in_taxon.yaml --infile=computed_only_in_taxon.tsv --outfile=computed_only_in_taxon.tmp.ofn &&\\\n428: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --template=../taxon_constraints/computed_never_in_taxon.yaml --infile=computed_never_in_taxon.tsv --outfile=computed_never_in_taxon.tmp.ofn &&\\\n429: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i computed_only_in_taxon.tmp.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ merge -i computed_never_in_taxon.tmp.ofn -o $@\n430: \n431: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.obo: imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.owl\n432: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.tmp.obo && grep -v '^owl-axioms' imports/go-computed-taxon-constraints.tmp.obo >$@\n433: \n434: imports/%_import.owl: imports/%_import_pre.owl\n435: \tcp $< $@\n436: \n437: imports/chebi_import.owl: bio-chebi.owl imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt $(SRC)\n438: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i bio-chebi.owl -T imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt --method BOT remove --term 'http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label' --term 'http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset' --term 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3' --select complement --select annotation-properties --signature true annotate -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n439: .PRECIOUS: imports/chebi_import.owl\n440: \n441: imports/%_import.obo: imports/%_import.owl\n442: \t$(ROBOT) convert --input $< --format obo --check false --output $@.tmp && grep -v ^owl-axioms: $@.tmp > $@\n443: \n444: # ----------------------------------------\n445: # CACHEING EXTERNAL ONTOLOGIES\n446: # ----------------------------------------\n447: \n448: # Fix external ontologies to specific release versions if necessary. These should be updated regularly! Otherwise use the standard PURL.\n449: CHEBI_SOURCE=http://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/chebi/archive/rel247/ontology/chebi.owl.gz # ChEBI is currently missing a version IRI\n450: CL_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/cl/releases/2025-01-08/cl-base.owl\n451: FAO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/fao/fao-base.owl\n452: PATO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/pato/pato-base.owl\n453: UBERON_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/uberon-base.owl\n454: WBBT_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/wbbt/wbbt-base.owl\n455: ECO_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/eco/eco-basic.owl\n456: OBA_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/oba/subsets/oba-basic.obo\n457: COB_SOURCE=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/cob.owl\n458: \n459: WGET_OUT = -O $@.tmp && cp $@.tmp $@ && touch $@\n460: \n461: mirror:\n462: \tmkdir $@\n463: \n464: # special case: download obo for speed for ncbitaxon.\n465: # note also that here we only trigger new downloads if ncbitaxon_terms.txt is touched\n466: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl: imports/ncbitaxon_terms.txt\n467: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon.obo $(WGET_OUT)\n468: .PRECIOUS: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl\n469: \n470: mirror/taxslim.owl: $(SRC)\n471: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n472: .PRECIOUS: mirror/taxslim.owl\n473: \n474: mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl: $(SRC)\n475: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n476: .PRECIOUS: mirror/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl\n477: \n478: mirror/pr-download.owl: $(SRC)\n479: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/pr.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n480: .PRECIOUS: mirror/pr-download.owl\n481: \n482: # special case: download gz for speed for chebi\n483: mirror/chebi-download.owl: $(SRC)\n484: \twget --no-check-certificate $(CHEBI_SOURCE) -O $@.tmp.gz && mv $@.tmp.gz $@.gz && gunzip -f $@.gz && touch $@\n485: .PRECIOUS: mirror/chebi-download.owl\n486: \n487: mirror/uberon-download.owl: $(SRC)\n488: \twget --no-check-certificate $(UBERON_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n489: .PRECIOUS: mirror/uberon-download.owl\n490: \n491: mirror/oba-download.owl: $(SRC)\n492: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBA_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n493: .PRECIOUS: mirror/oba-download.owl\n494: \n495: mirror/cl-download.owl: $(SRC)\n496: \twget --no-check-certificate $(CL_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n497: .PRECIOUS: mirror/cl-download.owl\n498: \n499: mirror/fao-download.owl: $(SRC)\n500: \twget --no-check-certificate $(FAO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n501: .PRECIOUS: mirror/fao-download.owl\n502: \n503: mirror/pato-download.owl: $(SRC)\n504: \twget --no-check-certificate $(PATO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n505: .PRECIOUS: mirror/pato-download.owl\n506: \n507: mirror/wbbt-download.owl: $(SRC)\n508: \twget --no-check-certificate $(WBBT_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n509: .PRECIOUS: mirror/wbbt-download.owl\n510: \n511: mirror/eco-download.owl: $(SRC)\n512: \twget --no-check-certificate $(ECO_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n513: .PRECIOUS: mirror/eco-download.owl\n514: \n515: mirror/cob-download.owl: $(SRC)\n516: \twget --no-check-certificate $(COB_SOURCE) $(WGET_OUT)\n517: .PRECIOUS: mirror/cob-download.owl\n518: \n519: mirror/ro-download.owl: $(SRC)\n520: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/ro.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n521: .PRECIOUS: mirror/ro-download.owl\n522: \n523: # general case: download remote OWL first\n524: mirror/%-download.owl: $(SRC)\n525: \twget --no-check-certificate $(OBO)/$*.owl $(WGET_OUT)\n526: .PRECIOUS: mirror/%-download.owl\n527: \n528: mirror/users.ttl:\n529: \tcurl -L -o $@.tmp 'https://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/users.ttl' &&\\\n530: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri 'http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/users.ttl' -o $@\n531: \n532: mirror/groups.ttl:\n533: \tcurl -L -o $@.tmp 'https://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/groups.ttl' &&\\\n534: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri 'http://snapshot.geneontology.org/metadata/groups.ttl' -o $@\n535: \n536: ../resources/rhea.rdf.gz:\n537: \tcurl -L -o $@ 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/rdf/rhea.rdf.gz'\n538: \n539: ../resources/rhea.rdf: ../resources/rhea.rdf.gz\n540: \t gunzip $< -c > $@\n541: \n542: ../resources/obsolete_ec.txt:\n543: \tcurl -L -o ../resources/enzyme.rdf 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/enzyme/enzyme.rdf' &&\\\n544: \tarq -q --data=../resources/enzyme.rdf --query=../sparql/query-obsolete-ec.sparql --results=tsv | tail -n +2 | sort >$@\n545: \n546: # bio-chebi.owl imports chebi and injects GCI axioms to conflate conjugate bases. See Hill et al\n547: bio-chebi.owl: mirror/chebi.owl chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn biochebi_gcis.ofn imports/substance_by_role.owl\n548: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn -i biochebi_gcis.ofn -i imports/substance_by_role.owl annotate --ontology-iri $(BASE)/extensions/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/extensions/$@ -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@\n549: \n550: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv:\n551: \twget 'ftp://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/tsv/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv' $(WGET_OUT)\n552: \n553: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_terms.txt: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv\n554: \ttail -n +2 $< | cut -f 2 | sort -n -u | sed 's/^/http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_/' >$@\n555: \n556: chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv\n557: \techo 'Ontology(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go/extensions/chebi-ph7_3-slim.ofn>' >$@.tmp &&\\\n558: \techo 'Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#SubsetProperty>))' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n559: \techo 'Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3>))' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n560: \techo 'SubAnnotationPropertyOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/go#chebi_ph7_3> <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#SubsetProperty>)' >>$@.tmp &&\\\n561: \ttail -n +2 $< | cut -f 2 | sort -n -u | sed 's/^/AnnotationAssertion(<http:\\/\\/www.geneontology.org\\/formats\\/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_/' | sed 's/$$/> <http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/go#chebi_ph7_3>)/' >>$@.tmp\n562: \techo ')' >>$@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n563: \n564: biochebi_gcis.tsv: ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv ../biochebi/biochebi_excludes.txt\n565: \techo 'source_chem\tstandard_chem' >$@.tmp &&\\\n566: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | awk -v FS='\\t' -v OFS='\\t' '{ if ($$1 != $$2) { print \"CHEBI:\"$$1, \"CHEBI:\"$$2} }' | grep -v -f ../biochebi/biochebi_excludes.txt >> $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n567: \n568: biochebi_gcis.ofn: biochebi_gcis.tsv ../biochebi/biochebi_gcis.yaml\n569: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) generate --obo-prefixes=true --generate-defined-class=true --template=../biochebi/biochebi_gcis.yaml --infile=$< --outfile=$@.tmp.ofn && mv $@.tmp.ofn $@\n570: \n571: ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt: imports/chebi_terms_combined.txt ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_terms.txt\n572: \tcat $^ >$@\n573: \n574: imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl: bio-chebi.owl ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt\n575: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< -T ../biochebi/go-lego-chebi-import-terms.txt --method BOT annotate -O $(BASE)/imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/imports/go-lego-chebi-import.owl -o $@\n576: \n577: .PRECIOUS: mirror/uberon.owl\n578: \n579: # Avoid filtering xref annotations. dbxrefs for three-letter codes are needed in Amigo.\n580: mirror/eco.owl: mirror/eco-download.owl\n581: \tcp $< $@\n582: \n583: # NCBITaxon must be special-cased due to the mixed-case prefix\n584: mirror/ncbitaxon.owl: mirror/ncbitaxon-download.owl\n585: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n586: \n587: # WBbt must be special-cased due to the mixed-case prefix\n588: # We are already downloading its base file, but there is still some duplicative RO content it it.\n589: mirror/wbbt.owl: mirror/wbbt-download.owl\n590: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/WBbt_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n591: \n592: mirror/ro.owl: mirror/ro-download.owl\n593: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_' --axioms internal --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n594: \n595: mirror/cob.owl: mirror/cob-download.owl\n596: \t# retain annotations for some ontologies which we don't import\n597: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --select 'COB:* MOP:* IAO:* OBI:* BFO:* PCO:* ENVO:*' --select complement --axioms annotation --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n598: \n599: mirror/%.owl: mirror/%-download.owl\n600: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --base-iri 'http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/$(shell echo $* | tr '[:lower:]' '[:upper:]')_' --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false remove --select imports --trim false annotate --ontology-iri $(OBO)/$@ --output $@\n601: # remove --term 'http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref' --trim false # need newer ROBOT version to do this without dropping definitions and synonyms\n602: #remove --drop-axiom-annotations all # need newer ROBOT version\n603: .PRECIOUS: mirror/%.owl\n604: \n605: # ----------------------------------------\n606: # CHEBI ROLES\n607: # ----------------------------------------\n608: \n609: HAS_ROLE = RO:0000087\n610: \n611: role.obo: mirror/chebi.owl\n612: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --term CHEBI:50906 --select \"self descendants\" --select \"complement\" --select \"classes\" annotate -O $(OBO)/go/chebi/role.owl -o $@\n613: \n614: imports/substance_by_role_equiv.obo: role.obo\n615: \t../util/make-substance-by-role.pl -s 'role' -r $(HAS_ROLE) $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n616: \n617: imports/substance_by_role.owl: imports/substance_by_role_equiv.obo\n618: \t$(ROBOT) reason -i $< --exclude-duplicate-axioms true --exclude-tautologies structural remove --axioms equivalent -o $@\n619: \n620: imports/substance_by_role.obo: imports/substance_by_role.owl\n621: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n622: \n623: # ----------------------------------------\n624: # IMPORTED AND TRANSFERRED RHEA AXIOMS\n625: # ----------------------------------------\n626: \n627: rhea.ttl: ../sparql/construct-rhea-reactions.sparql ../resources/rhea.rdf\n628: \tarq -q --data=../resources/rhea.rdf --query=../sparql/construct-rhea-reactions.sparql --results=turtle >$@\n629: \n630: extensions/rhea-reactions.ttl: rhea.ttl\n631: \t$(SCALA_CLI) ../util/construct_rhea_ontology.sc -- $< rhea-reactions.ofn && \\\n632: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i rhea-reactions.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n633: \n634: extensions/rhea-reactions-simple.ttl: rhea.ttl\n635: \t$(SCALA_CLI) ../util/construct_rhea_ontology_simplified.sc -- $< rhea-reactions-simple.ofn && \\\n636: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i rhea-reactions-simple.ofn -O $(BASE)/$@ -V $(RELEASE_URIBASE)/$@ -o $@\n637: \n638: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl: extensions/rhea-reactions-simple.ttl $(SRC)\n639: \t$(SCALA_CLI) ../util/transfer_rhea_relations.sc -- $< $(SRC) catalog-v001.xml $@.tmp && \\\n640: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp -O $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n641: \n642: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.obo: imports/go-catalytic-activities-participants.owl\n643: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@\n644: \n645: # ----------------------------------------\n646: # MAPPINGS\n647: # ----------------------------------------\n648: EXTERNAL2GO_DBS = EC KEGG_REACTION MetaCyc Reactome RESID UM-BBD_enzymeID UM-BBD_pathwayID UM-BBD_reactionID Wikipedia RHEA\n649: \n650: # See : https://github.com/geneontology/go-site/issues/688\n651: # Manually add all ID spaces here; only do this for xrefs that are managed within the obo file.\n652: .PHONY: generate-mappings\n653: generate-mappings: $(ONT)-pre.ofn\n654: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --external-mappings-files -o external2go --label-prefix GO: --externals $(EXTERNAL2GO_DBS)\n655: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/interpro2go -O external2go/interpro2go\n656: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/pfam2go -O external2go/pfam2go\n657: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/pirsf2go -O external2go/pirsf2go\n658: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/prints2go -O external2go/prints2go\n659: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/prosite2go -O external2go/prosite2go\n660: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/smart2go -O external2go/smart2go\n661: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/uniprotkb_kw2go -O external2go/uniprotkb_kw2go\n662: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/uniprotkb_sl2go -O external2go/uniprotkb_sl2go\n663: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/unirule2go -O external2go/unirule2go\n664: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/hamap2go -O external2go/hamap2go\n665: \twget https://mirror.geneontology.io/rfam2go -O external2go/rfam2go\n666: \n667: # ----------------------------------------\n668: # TAXON GROUPINGS\n669: # ----------------------------------------\n670: \n671: imports/go-taxon-groupings.owl: imports/go-taxon-groupings-edit.owl imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl\n672: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl reason -r jfact --axiom-generators \"SubClass EquivalentClass DisjointClasses\" query --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-1.ru --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-2.ru --update ../sparql/delete-redundant-disjoints-3.ru --update ../sparql/add-taxon-disjoints.ru --update ../sparql/add-in-taxon-disjoints.ru unmerge -i imports/ncbitaxon_import.owl -o $@\n673: \n674: imports/go-taxon-groupings.obo: imports/go-taxon-groupings.owl\n675: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -o $@.tmp.obo && grep -v ^owl-axioms $@.tmp.obo > $@\n676: \n677: # ----------------------------------------\n678: # VALIDATION\n679: # ----------------------------------------\n680: \n681: # these live in the ../sparql directory, and have suffix -violation.sparql\n682: # adding the name here will make the violation check live\n683: \n684: VCHECKS = equivalent-classes trailing-whitespace owldef-self-reference synonym-label-match replacedby-obsolete replacedby-namespace missing-namespace duplicate-exact-synonym duplicate-synonym non-IRI-value non-anyURI-value obsolete-definition definition-constraints one-to-one-xrefs-by-subject one-to-one-xrefs-by-value xref-syntax\n685: \n686: # run all violation checks\n687: VARGS = $(foreach V,$(VCHECKS), $(SPARQLDIR)/$V-violation.sparql)\n688: sparql_test: go-edit-filtered-xrefs.ofn reasoned.ofn\n689: \t$(ROBOT) verify --input $< --queries $(VARGS) -O reports/\n690: \t# These purposely aren't checking problems in imports\n691: \t$(ROBOT) verify --input reasoned.ofn --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/multiple-class-links-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/missing_superclass-violation.sparql $(SPARQLDIR)/different-namespace-violation.sparql -O reports/\n692: \n693: # use this to run tests on an individual basis\n694: reports/%-violation.csv: $(SRC)\n695: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*-violation.sparql $@\n696: \n697: check-obsolete-references-including-imports: reasoned.ofn\n698: \t$(ROBOT) merge --input reasoned.ofn verify --queries $(SPARQLDIR)/obsolete-reference-violation.sparql -O reports/\n699: \n700: ## Datalog validations\n701: go-edit.facts: $(SRC)\n702: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(SRC) -o go-edit.facts.ttl &&\\\n703: \triot -q --nocheck --output ntriples go-edit.facts.ttl | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ /\\t/' | sed 's/ \\.$$//' >$@\n704: \n705: ../resources/rhea-relationships.tsv:\n706: \twget 'https://ftp.expasy.org/databases/rhea/tsv/rhea-relationships.tsv' -O - | tail -n +2 >$@\n707: \n708: datalog-violations.tsv: go-edit.facts ../resources/obsolete_ec.txt\n709: \tsouffle ../util/ontology-qc.dl &&\\\n710: \t( [ -s $@ ] && { cat $@; exit 1; } || true ) # exit with an error if the output is not empty\n711: \n712: reports/neo-violations.report: $(GO_LEGO).owl\n713: \t$(ROBOT) report --input $(GO_LEGO).owl --tdb true --tdb-directory tdb/ -k true -p ../sparql/neo/profile.txt -o $@ --print 50 -v\n714: \n715: # intermediate files in this target must be lexically, not numerically sorted, for use with comm\n716: # terms listed in ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt are exempted from the pH 7.3 requirement\n717: chebi_pH_7_3_check: reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt\n718: \ttail -n +2 reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv | sed 's/<http:\\/\\/purl.obolibrary.org\\/obo\\/CHEBI_//g' | sed 's/>//g' | sort -u >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n719: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | cut -f 1 | sort -u >tmp_mapped_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n720: \ttail -n +2 ../biochebi/chebi_pH7_3_mapping.tsv | cut -f 2 | sort -u >tmp_7_3_chebi_nums.txt &&\\\n721: \tgrep '^CHEBI:' ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt | sed 's/^CHEBI://' | sort -u >tmp_chebi_allow_nums.txt &&\\\n722: \tcomm -23 tmp_referenced_chebi_nums.txt tmp_7_3_chebi_nums.txt >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3.txt &&\\\n723: \tcomm -23 tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3.txt tmp_chebi_allow_nums.txt >tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt &&\\\n724: \tif [ -s 'tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt' ]; then echo \"ERROR: CHEBI IDs should be mapped to pH 7.3 (or added to ../biochebi/chebi-allow.txt):\" && cat tmp_referenced_chebi_nums_not_7_3_not_allowed.txt && exit 1; else exit 0; fi\n725: \n726: # ----------------------------------------\n727: # REPORTS\n728: # ----------------------------------------\n729: # We use `robot query` to generate TSVs from SPARQL\n730: \n731: REPORTS = owl-stats basic-report class-count-by-prefix edges labels xrefs obsoletes synonyms\n732: REPORT_ARGS = $(foreach V,$(REPORTS),-s $(SPARQLDIR)/$V.sparql reports/$V.tsv)\n733: all_reports: go.owl\n734: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< $(REPORT_ARGS)\n735: \n736: #all_src_reports: $(patsubst %,reports/src-%.tsv,$(REPORTS))\n737: \n738: reports/%.tsv: go.owl $(SPARQLDIR)/%.sparql $(REPORTDIR)\n739: \t$(ROBOT) -vv query -f tsv -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n740: reports/src-%.tsv: go-edit.obo $(SPARQLDIR)/%.sparql $(REPORTDIR)\n741: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< -s $(SPARQLDIR)/$*.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n742: \n743: reports/referenced_chebi_terms.tsv: $(SRC)\n744: \t$(ROBOT) query -f tsv -i $< --query $(SPARQLDIR)/referenced-chebi-terms.sparql $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n745: \n746: # ----------------------------------------\n747: # DESIGN PATTERNS\n748: # ----------------------------------------\n749: \n750: ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS=$(wildcard ../design_patterns/*.yaml)\n751: ALL_PATTERN_NAMES=$(patsubst ../design_patterns/%.yaml,%,$(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS))\n752: ALL_PATTERN_TSVS=$(patsubst %.yaml,%.tsv,$(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS))\n753: \n754: # Currently not rebuilt automatically; waiting for updated dosdp-tools in ODK\n755: imports/go-pattern-conformance.ttl: reasoned.ofn $(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS)\n756: \trm -f ../design_patterns/*.tsv &&\\\n757: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) query --obo-prefixes=true --batch-patterns=\"$(ALL_PATTERN_NAMES)\" --template=../design_patterns --outfile=../design_patterns --ontology=reasoned.ofn --catalog=catalog-v001.xml --reasoner=elk --parallelism=4 --output-conformance=$@.tmp &&\\\n758: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@.tmp --ontology-iri $(BASE)/$@ -o $@\n759: \n760: pattern-docs: imports/go-pattern-conformance.ttl reasoned.ofn $(ALL_PATTERN_YAMLS) $(ALL_PATTERN_TSVS)\n761: \trm -f ../../docs/patterns/*.md &&\\\n762: \t$(DOSDP_TOOLS) docs --obo-prefixes=true --batch-patterns=\"$(ALL_PATTERN_NAMES)\" --template=../design_patterns --outfile=../../docs/patterns --infile=../design_patterns --data-location-prefix='https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/tree/master/src/design_patterns/' --ontology=reasoned.ofn --catalog=catalog-v001.xml\n\n(End of file - total 762 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"all: stage_release\n\nSHELL=./stamp.sh\n\n# ----------------------------------------\n# CORE VARIABLES\n# ----------------------------------------\n\n# base URI for all OBO library ontologies\nOBO=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo\n\n# OBO name of this ontology (always lowercase)\nONT=go\n\n# Base URL for ontology\nBASE=$(OBO)/$(ONT)\n\n# Source file edited by editors\nSRC=$(ONT)-edit.obo\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/Makefile","time":{"start":1778467078105,"end":1778467078114}},"id":"prt_e14e5fc7f001Afikw71Opy6tnl","sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","messageID":"msg_e14e5f0db0016tGFXPW7OrMwso"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1778467078167,"sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","part":{"id":"prt_e14e60015001tlT6gDP8HsOIrQ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"71946e1059f195197155070bce5592452e9a82bc","messageID":"msg_e14e5f0db0016tGFXPW7OrMwso","sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20050,"input":19905,"output":145,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.0040535}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778467083591,"sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","part":{"id":"prt_e14e61545001mbltX8RcVclI3B","messageID":"msg_e14e6003e001o2JPClYKZZl0Qs","sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","snapshot":"71946e1059f195197155070bce5592452e9a82bc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778467096163,"sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-9b83519ab8d3f04c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"research"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"research\">\n# Skill: research\n\n## Context\n\nYou can use normal web search tools to find relevant literature. You can also use trusted encyclopedic sources such\nas wikipedia but it's good to follow up with the publications themselves. All research must be summarized in a file RESEARCH.md.\nThis file is NOT to be committed, however, it MUST be communicated back appropriately to the user.\n\nRemember, most of the time you are likely to be running in a GitHub actions context, when triggered from an issue (via a `@dragon-ai-agent` invocation). If this is the case, the RESEARCH.md contents\nshould be copied onto the issue comments. Otherwise, the user has no way of seeing the RESEARCH.md file, as it disappears alongside the temporary github actions workspace.\n\nThis is especially true if the user asks you explicitly to research a topic  - they want to see the full report! Even if you make the RESEARCH.md as part of a broader task, it is good to post the contents.\n\nYou can editorialize if need be\n\n## When to invoke\n\nUse this appropriately. If the request is to fix a typo in a synonym or definition, there is no need to do research (write as N/A in any checklists). Similarly if the request pertains to a trivial compositional term then research is not required. But if there is any nuanced biology involved, it is good to do the appropriate level of research.\n\nAlways bear in mind:\n\n- GO is pan-species; while human relevance is good, don't assume the term will only be used for human biology\n- GO is primarily interested in evolved molecular and cellular biology, and not pleiotropic phenotypes\n- For ontology terms, recent reviews are often better than older references, or references that focus on specific experimental results\n- Encyclopedic and book references are perfectly fine for high level biology (e.g. \"nucleus\"); but even for well understood processes (e.g. apoptosis), recent reviews are favored\n\n## Deep Research\n\nFor detailed searches, you can do deep research queries:\n\n```\ndeep-research-client research --provider perplexity \"<DETAILED RESEARCH QUESTION HERE>\" --output results.md --separate-citations citations.md\n```\n\nThis will take around 5 minutes or so.\n\nIf the user wants to do more extensive research, or if perplexity credits are exhaustive, then use the `cyberian` provider:\n\n\n```\ndeep-research-client research --provider cyberian ....\n```\n\n## Caching PMIDs and DOIs\n\nYou can use `linkml-reference-validator` to cache references. This is in your path. Note that this will not always work for full texts.\n\nExample:\n`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:28318978`\n==> writes to `references_cache/PMID_28318978.md`\n\nAlways use this to check that there are no typos or hallucinations with reference IDs. If the title or abstract doesn't match with what the reference is purportedly supporting, there is likely a typo or hallucination.\n\nNote that `references_cache` should NOT be checked back in to git.\n\n## Incorporating research results back into your work\n\nPMIDs are preferred for most purposes. These are usually written as CURIEs, e.g. `PMID:123456`. Next best are DOIs, also curies `DOI:<doi>`\n\nFor GO, usually the best place to include citations is in definition provenance; e.g\n\n```obo\ndef: \"<genus and differentia>. <additional info>\" [PMID:nnnn]\n```\n\nBut you should ALWAYS include more detailed summaries of publications in RESEARCH.md\n\nEntries in RESEARCH.md should have blocks in the following format:\n\n```\n## <PMID:nnnnnnn> \"<TITLE>\"\n\n<brief summary>\n\n* SUPPORT: <PMID:nnnnnn> \"<EXACT excerpt from publication>\"\n    - finding 1\n    - finding 2\n    - ...\n\ni.e. `^ SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)$\"` all on one line, with no newlines between the `\"\"`s\n\nYou MUST validate the supporting text like this:\n\n`linkml-reference-validator validate text-file -r 'SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)\"' -t 2 -R 1 RESEARCH.md`\n\nIn some cases, if a full text is not available and support cannot be found in the abstract, but support came from deep research, you can say:\n\n* NO_FULL_TEXT: <PMID:nnnn> <say how you obtained the information>\n    - finding 1\n    - finding 2\n    - ...\n\n## What to at the end of the research phase\n\nRemember that if the user is communicating with you via github action they will not see the RESEARCH.md file\n\nOn completion, this skill should produce a complete RESEARCH.md, with no fabricated results.\n\nBase directory for this skill: file:///home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/research\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"research","dir":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/research","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: research","time":{"start":1778467096150,"end":1778467096162}},"id":"prt_e14e64489001XeG6eZXWCl1knm","sessionID":"ses_1eb1b9533ffeChgjeZ6kjtREo7","messageID":"msg_e14e6003e001o2JPClYKZZl0Qs"}}
